# Keep the Docker build context small and reproducible. The app image installs
# the workspace graph from the committed manifests + lockfile and builds inside
# the container, so none of the host's installed/built artifacts are needed.

# Dependencies (reinstalled in-image from package-lock.json)
**/node_modules

# Build output (rebuilt in-image)
**/dist
**/build
**/*.tsbuildinfo
dashboard/dist

# Env & secrets — never bake host secrets into an image layer
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/*.local

# Local state / volumes
.data/
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output

# VCS & CI
.git
.gitignore
.github/

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Tooling & agent state
.claude/

# Docs & meta not needed at build time
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# Logs
**/*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
